org.jcvi.jillion.trace.fastq

Interface FastqWriter

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable

    public interface FastqWriter
extends Closeable
    FastqWriter is an interface that handles writing out FastqRecords.

    dkatzel

      • write

        void write(FastqRecord record)
    throws IOException
        Write the given FastqRecord out.
        Parameters:
        record - the FastqRecord to write; can not be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem writing out the FastqRecord.
        NullPointerException - if record is null.

      • write

        default void write(FastqRecord record,
                   Range trimRange)
            throws IOException
        Write the given FastqRecord out.
        Implementation Note:
        The default implementation is given below, but implementations may override this method to provide a more efficient version: 
         if(trimRange==null){
     write(record);
     return;
 }
 write(record.getId(), 
                    record.getNucleotideSequence()
                            .toBuilder()
                            .trim(trimRange)
                            .build(), 
                    record.getQualitySequence()
                            .toBuilder()
                            .trim(trimRange)
                            .build(),
                 record.getComment());
        Parameters:
        record - the FastqRecord to write; can not be null.
        trimRange - the Range to use to trim the nucleotide and quality sequences. If the trimRange is null, then the whole sequence is written.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem writing out the FastqRecord.
        NullPointerException - if record is null.
        Since:
        5.2

        Write the given id, NucleotideSequence and QualitySequence out as a FastqRecord without a comment.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the record to be written.
        nucleotides - the NucleotideSequence to be written.
        qualities - the QualitySequence to be written.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem writing out the record.
        NullPointerException - if either id, nucleotides or qualities are null.

      • write

        default void write(String id,
                   NucleotideSequence sequence,
                   QualitySequence qualities,
                   String optionalComment)
            throws IOException
        Write the given id and {NucleotideSequence and QualitySequence out as a FastqRecord along with the optional comment.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the record to be written.
        sequence - the NucleotideSequence to be written.
        qualities - the QualitySequence to be written.
        optionalComment - comment to write, if this value is null, then no comment will be written.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem writing out the record.
        NullPointerException - if either id, nucleotides or qualities are null.

      • adapt

        static FastqWriter adapt(FastqWriter delegate,
                         Function<FastqRecord,FastqRecord> adapter)
        Create a new FastqWriter that will wrap the given fastqWriter and intercept any calls to write() to allow the record to be transformed in some way. For example, to change the id or modify or trim the sequences; or even skip the record entirely.
        Parameters:
        delegate - the writer to delegate the actual writing to this writer will be called after each record is adapted.
        adapter - a Function that is given the input FastqRecord to be written and will return a possibly new FastqRecord to actually write. If the function returns null then the record is skipped.
        Returns:
        a new FastqWriter; will never be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if any parameter is null.
        Since:
        5.3

      • write

        static void write(FastqFileDataStore datastore,
                  File outputFile)
           throws IOException
        Write the contents of the given datastore to the given output file. The output fastq file written will use the same FastqQualityCodec as was used in the input fastq of the datastore.
        API Note:
        this is the same as write(datastore, outputFile, datastore.getQualityCodec()).
        Parameters:
        datastore - the FastqFileDataStore to write out; can not be null.
        outputFile - the output file to write the resulting Fastq file to.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there are any problems writing out the file.
        NullPointerException - if any parameter is null.
        Since:
        5.3

      • write

        static void write(FastqDataStore datastore,
                  File outputFile,
                  FastqQualityCodec codec)
           throws IOException
        Write the contents of the given datastore to the given output file. The output fastq file written will use the same FastqQualityCodec as was used in the input fastq of the datastore.
        Parameters:
        datastore - the FastqDataStore to write out; can not be null.
        outputFile - the output file to write the resulting Fastq file to.
        coec - the FastqQualityCodec to use when writing out the output fastq file.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there are any problems writing out the file.
        NullPointerException - if any parameter is null.
        Since:
        5.3
